          <tr><td><strong>Cook's Corner</strong></td><td>Shopping area, suburban feel, good parking, grocery traffic</td><td>$14-17</td><td>Family customers, convenience-driven</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Route 1</strong></td><td>Highway access, regional draw, lower rent, drive-in customers</td><td>$12-15</td><td>Customers from surrounding towns, volume positioning</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Location Tip" type="tip">
      Maine Street in downtown Brunswick puts you closest to the college crowd. If your brand targets young adults and quality-focused consumers, that location is worth the premium rent. Route 1 is better for capturing driving traffic from surrounding towns like Topsham, Bath, and Lisbon Falls. Cook's Corner serves the suburban family demographic that prefers convenient parking over walkable downtown character.
    </Callout>

    <section>
